article.headline: Anderson scores 26, Central Arkansas downs Lipscomb 96-86
article.description: — Tucker Anderson had 26 points in Central Arkansas' 96-86 victory over Lipscomb on Thursday night.
article.linkText: Anderson scores 26, Central Arkansas downs Lipscomb 96-86
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- — Tucker Anderson had 26 points in Central Arkansas' 96-86 victory over Lipscomb on Thursday night. Anderson shot 8 for 12 (6 for 10 from 3-point range) and 4 of 4 from the free throw line for the Bears (7-13, 3-1 Atlantic Sun Conference). Masai Olowokere scored 16 points while going 5 of 6 (4 for 4 from 3-point range). Daniel Sofield had 15 points and finished 4 of 4 from 3-point range and 3 for 3 from the line. The Bisons (11-8, 2-2) were led by Cody Head, who recorded 20 points. Lipscomb also got 15 points from A.J McGinnis. Owen McCormack also recorded 14 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
